This C++ program demonstrates various string manipulation techniques using the string class from the C++ Standard Library.
It covers operations such as concatenation, substring extraction, finding substrings, replacing parts of strings, inserting strings, erasing parts of strings, and converting case
Concatenation: Combines two strings.
Substring Extraction: Retrieves a specific part of a string.
Finding a Substring: Locates the position of a substring within a string.
Replacing a Substring: Substitutes a substring with another string.
Inserting a String: Inserts a string at a specified position.
Erasing a Substring: Removes a part of the string.
Changing Case: Converts the string to uppercase and lowercase.
